#  Messy Dataset Cleaning & EDA ‚Äî Nashville Housing

This project demonstrates how to clean and analyze a messy real-world dataset using Python. The dataset contains housing records from Nashville, Tennessee, and includes common data quality issues such as missing values, inconsistent formatting, duplicate entries, and unstructured text fields.

---

##  Dataset
- **Source**: [Nashville Housing Data](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tmthyjames/nashville-housing-data)
- **File**: `data/nashville_housing.csv`

---

##  Python Libraries Used
- pandas
- numpy
- matplotlib

---

##  Cleaning Steps
- Column name standardization
- Handling missing values
- Date conversion (`sale_date`)
- Removing duplicates
- Text cleanup (`owner_name`, `property_address`, `land_use`)

---

##  EDA Visuals
- Bar chart: Property type distribution
- Pie chart: Top 5 land use categories
- Histogram: Sale price distribution
- Correlation heatmap
- Year-wise sale trend

